image.caption: Oregon's Lexi Bando, 10, Sabrina Ionescu, 20, and Oti Gildon, 32 wave to fans after beating Minnesota 101-73 and earning a trip to the Sweet 16 after their second-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Sabrina Ionescu drives around Minnesota's, Taiye Bello (left) and Gadiva Hubbard during the first half in a second-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Ruthy Hebard, left, and Justine Hall, right, battle Minnesota's Kenisha Bell for a loose ball during the 2nd quarter of their second-round game in the NCAA women’s college basketball tournament in Eugene, Ore., Sunday, March 18, 2018. (AP Photo/Chris Pietsch)

Oregon's Ruthy Hebard drives around Minnesota's Jessie Edwards during the first half in a second-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Satou Sabally, left, battles Minnesota's Kenisha Bell, center left, Oregon's Ruthy Hebard center and Minnesota's Destiny Pitts for a loose ball during the first half of their second-round game in the NCAA women’s college basketball tournament in Eugene, Ore., Sunday, March 18, 2018. (AP Photo/Chris Pietsch)

Oregon's Sabrina Ionescu scores between Minnesota's, Taiye Bello (left) and Destiny Pitts during the first half in a second-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Lexi Bando scores around Minnesota's Bryanna Fernstrom during the first half in a second-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Satou Sabally (left), Sabrina Ionescu, Ruthy Hebard, and Maite Cazorla overwhelm Minnesota's Taiye Bello during the second half in a second-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Ruthy Hebard, 24, celebrates her score with Sabrina Ionescu (left) and Maite Cazorla during the first half in a second-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Maite Cazorla, left, Sabrina Ionescu, center left, Justine Hall, and Satou Sabally a buzzer beating three-point shot by Ionescu during the first half of their second-round game against Minnesota in the NCAA women’s college basketball tournament in Eugene, Ore., Sunday, March 18, 2018. (AP Photo/Chris Pietsch)

Oregon's Ruthy Hebard splits the Minnesota defense en route to the Ducks 101-73 win in a second-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Minnesota's Kenisha Bell, 23, is helped off the floor by Destiny Pitt's, 3, as the Ducks downed the Golden Gophers 101-73 in their second-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Maite Cazorla drives around Minnesota defenders, Jessie Edwards (left) and Kenisha Bell during the first half in a second-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Sabrina Ionescu (left) Lexie Bando, Salou Salably, Maite Cazorla, and Ruthy Hebard watch time run out at the Ducks beat Minnesota 101-73 and advance to the Sweet 16 after their second-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon women's head coach, Kelly Graves, embraces with his family in the stands at Matthew Knight Arena after his team beat Minnesota 101-73 and earned another trip to the Sweet 16 on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

University of Oregon athletic director, Rob Mullens, is all smiles after the Ducks handled Minnesota 101-73 and earned a trip to the Sweet 16 after their second-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon players Sabrina Ionescu, left, Lexi Bando, and Satou Sabally start the celebration from the bench with their teammates as the second tick away in their 101-73 over Minnesota in the second-round game in the NCAA women’s college basketball tournament in Eugene, Ore., Sunday, March 18, 2018. (AP Photo/Chris Pietsch)

A Sweet 16 bound Oregon bench erupts in the final minutes of their 101-73 second-round game win over Minnesota in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)

Oregon's Ruthy Hebard (left), and Sabrina Ionescu wave to fans after beating Minnesota 101-73 and earning a trip to the Sweet 16 after their second-round game in the NCAA women's college basketball tournament at Matthew Knight Arena on Sunday, March 18, 2018. (Collin Andrew/The Register-Guard)
